task.summary: fixed bug when children returned None
since 1 step lookahead gameover exists, prioritize choosing true gameovers vs. a win_status when possible
turned sim info into dict, only penalize if opponent not in home territory
pseudo-pruning now. eval children in batches
turned off reexpansion checks, pick the highest NN prob guaranteed child
fixed caution referencing child game board instead of parent game board
a little more filtering and extra true wins/losses for visits that get a win_status.
guarding home better, check all home rows that can capture for game saving moves.
guarding home better, check all home rows that can capture for game saving moves.
search best if under threshold (diff for each player), put height back into penalty judgment
lower confidence bound for exploiting best child
changed NN scaling for UCT WR choice to 1/4 as opposed to 1/10
made UCT select code more readable
reduced restrictions on choosing true losers.
tightened up the NN Eval code
passing async update lock as a function parameter instead of using it as a global
added a move selection filter so low probability outliers with high mean action values can be chosen (rare, but happens)
only sending back game saving moves if next move is a game over, found out the tree search stalls on player because the threshold leaves out nodes that need to be checked for a win status.

switched back to old config (18% better WR). Manually garbage collecting. Added exit statements and context managers. Still trying to figure out why the first game gets so many nodes while subsequent ones don't
